      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "INSPECTION (2) continues to race in super honest form hitting the frame at two of eight starts runs and has won two of last three, the latest winning (26.07) over 460m at Warragul. Has never been out of the money in three starts this course and distance. On top here on best form and expected to feature. PAW FABLE (7) was safely held last time out, finishing seventh at Shepparton over 450m behind Manager (25.65) in a Grade 4/5. Was in the money prior to that. Better than last start and can bounce back. FLAT OUT FREDDY (3) turned in a plain run last time when fifth at Warrnambool over 450m behind Settle For Less (25.97) in a Grade 5. Was in the money prior to that. Yet to score from this box but has never missed the frame in two starts. Expected to feature in the finish. DEVINGTON (4) deserves plenty of thought at his first run at this circuit.",
